        "content": [
          "The SUBJUNCTIVE is a mood, not a tense.",
          "It expresses wishes, doubts, emotions,",
          "and things that aren't certain facts.",
          "",
          "FORMATION — flip the vowel:          Press 1",
          "-AR verbs get -E endings:",
          "hablar → hable, hables, hable,",
          "hablemos, hablen",
          "",
          "-ER/-IR verbs get -A endings:        Press 2",
          "comer → coma, comas, coma,",
          "comamos, coman",
          "",
          "TRIGGER: que + subjunctive           Press 3",
          "Quiero que vengas.",
          "(I want you to come.) — stated desire/want",
          "Espero que estés bien.",
          "(I hope you're well.) — stated hope/wish"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lección diecinueve",
        "pronunciation_mappings": {
          "1": "hable, hables, hable, hablemos, hablen",
          "2": "coma, comas, coma, comamos, coman",
          "3": "quiero que vengas, espero que estés bien"
        }
      },
      {
        "page": 2,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "WHEN TO USE SUBJUNCTIVE:",
          "",
          "AFTER WISHES/DESIRES:                Press 1",
          "Quiero que estudies.",
          "(I want you to study.)",
          "AFTER EMOTIONS:                      Press 2",
          "Me alegra que estés aquí.",
          "(I'm glad that you're here.)",
          "AFTER DOUBT/DENIAL:                  Press 3",
          "No creo que sea verdad.",
          "(I don't think it's true.)",
          "AFTER OJALÁ (I hope/if only):        Press 4",
          "Ojalá llueva mañana.",
          "(I hope it rains tomorrow.)",
          "",
          "KEY: If there's certainty, use",
          "indicative. If there's uncertainty,",
          "desire, or emotion, use subjunctive."
        ],
